com.ibm.hrl.xmleditor.extension.xsl
Class XSLHandler

java.lang.Object
  |
  +--com.ibm.hrl.xmleditor.extension.xsl.XSLHandler
public class XSLHandler
extends java.lang.Object
implements ToolHandler

An extension to Xeena that implements an XSL Processor. It takes a XML document as input, and invokes the Xalan tool on it. A full description of the Xalan project is available on the apache site.

init

public void init(java.lang.String _data)
Asks the XSL Handler to initialize its dialog using the data provided in the DTD configuration file. If data is provided it should follow the format (all properties are optional and separated by new-lines): 
  
 default.viewer=<absolute-file>
 default.stylesheet=<file-or-url>
 default.result=<file>

 For example:
 
 default.stylesheet=http://ps231-17.haifa.ibm.com/demo.xsl
 default.result=d:/example.html
 default.viewer=c:/Program Files/Netscape/Communicator/Program/netscape.exe
You may provide non absolute files for the stylesheet and result. In this case the value will be concatenated to the path of the xml document this handler is working on.
Parameters:
_data - the String provided in the DTD configuration file.
See Also:
Extension.init(java.lang.String)
